  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 1446836957184
    m_Localized: Stater
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947072
    m_Localized: Large Celtic gold stater.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446874705920
    m_Localized: Eighth of a Stater
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947073
    m_Localized: 1/8 of a Celtic gold stater.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446874705921
    m_Localized: Aluminum commemorative ring
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947074
    m_Localized: An aluminum commemorative ring from 1914, likely made by a soldier
      as a memento of the beginning of World War I.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446874705922
    m_Localized: Denarius
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947075
    m_Localized: 'Silver Denarius of the Roman Republic, Monier: M. Atilius Saranus,
      148BCE, 19.5mm, 3.8g'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900224
    m_Localized: A medallion made from a coin
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947076
    m_Localized: The medallion is a reworked silver coin from 1765. On the reverse
      side of the medallion, there is a depiction of the bust of Bavarian Elector
      Maximilian III Joseph Wittelsbach (1727-1777).
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900225
    m_Localized: Boar Figurine
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947077
    m_Localized: "Bronze boar figurine from the La T\xE8ne period."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900226
    m_Localized: Celtic bracelet
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947078
    m_Localized: 'Simple bronze bracelet from the Celtic period. Diameter: 6,7 cm.
      Weight: ca. 50 g.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900227
    m_Localized: Small bronze hook
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947079
    m_Localized: "A bronze hook of uncertain use from the La T\xE8ne period, ca.10
      cm, ca.70g."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900228
    m_Localized: Part of an axe
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947080
    m_Localized: 'A fragment of a bronze axe from over 1000 years before our era.
      Weight: ca. 235 g.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900229
    m_Localized: Possible Bronze Age Ingot
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947081
    m_Localized: A complete copper alloy probable ingot of possible Bronze Age or
      later dating (2300 BC to 1500 AD). Weight approximately 46.2 grams.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900230
    m_Localized: A cartridge case from 1936
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947082
    m_Localized: An incomplete cartridge case (7.92 x 57 mm) from the Czechoslovakian
      company Sellier & Bellot, dated 1936.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900231
    m_Localized: Rifle Cartridge Case
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947083
    m_Localized: The ammunition evidently misfired, as the bullet is still intact,
      and the primer is damaged.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900232
    m_Localized: Remainder of a shotgun shell
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947084
    m_Localized: Heavily damaged remainder of a shotgun shell for a hunting shotgun.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900233
    m_Localized: Small calibre cartridge case
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947085
    m_Localized: An old and damaged small-caliber cartridge case.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900234
    m_Localized: Copper kreuzer
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947086
    m_Localized: 'Maria Theresa Kreuzer from the year 1761. Diameter: 25 mm. Weight:
      11 grams.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1446878900235
    m_Localized: 1 Czechoslovak koruna
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3871970947087
    m_Localized: 'Coins of Czechoslovakia. Currency unit: koruna. Year of issue:
      1959. Material: copper, aluminum, manganese (91+8+1). Edge: ribbed. Diameter:
      23 mm. Weight: 4 g.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
